<HEAD>Two Policemen Killed In Separate Shootings</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LARRY NEUMEISTER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An undercover policeman was shot and killed during a drug buy and a patrolman was slain while responding to a medical emergency in separate incidents Tuesday night, police said. The undercover officer was shot in the head and chest at 7:11 p.m. as he and another undercover officer tried to buy a gram of cocaine at an apartment just west of <LOCATION> Central </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Park </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION>, police Commissioner <PERSON> Benjamin </PERSON> <PERSON> Ward </PERSON> said. In a gunfight that followed, a drug suspect was killed, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON> told a news conference. A second suspect was arrested as he fled the building and a third eluded police. The second officer was shot in the chest and stomach at 9:45 p.m. as he and his partner were getting out of their patrol car in <LOCATION> Harlem </LOCATION> while responding to a medical emergency, said Officer <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Conde </LOCATION>, a police spokeswoman. Both of the officers died at hospitals, said Sgt. <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Donnell </PERSON>, a police spokesman. The dead policemen's identities were not released. In the first shooting, two men escorted the officers to the apartment to buy drugs from a third man, and one of the three accused the officers of being undercover police, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON> said. One of the three pulled out a .357 - caliber handgun and shot the After the gunfight that ensued, the other officer ran into the street and alerted backup police. The officer slain in the drug case was 26 years old and had been a member of the force since 1984, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON> said. Mayor <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> I. </PERSON> <PERSON> Koch </PERSON>, who accompanied <PERSON> Ward </PERSON> at the news conference, called the shooting `` an enormous tragedy. The partner -LRB- is -RRB- terribly shaken. It's really overwhelming.'' The officers had been attempting to carry out a buy-and-bust raid, in which police purchase drugs from suspects, then arrest them.
