<HEAD>APME Recognizes 288 Papers, Stations For Contributions</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-APME Awards</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Associated Press Managing Editors association has awarded 288 citations to newspapers and broadcast stations for outstanding contributions to the <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> report. The awards were presented Tuesday by <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Morrissey </PERSON>, metro editor of The <LOCATION> Flint </LOCATION> -LRB- <LOCATION> Mich. </LOCATION> -RRB- Journal and a member of the <ORGANIZATION> APME </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Citations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, at the annual APME convention. The <ORGANIZATION> APME </ORGANIZATION> is made up of managing editors and other news executives of the 1,463 member newspapers of the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION>, the world's largest newsgathering organization The <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> is a cooperative agency whose members provide coverage of news in their areas for distribution through AP bureaus in their states. The citations are in three categories _ news, newsphoto and news-newsphoto. Newspapers and broadcast stations cited in each category are:
