n and soldiers. The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> considers <ORGANIZATION> El </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Salvador </ORGANIZATION> one of its closest allies in <LOCATION> Central </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>. The protesters maintain the leftist guerrillas are willing to negotiate an end to the fighting but that the <LOCATION> Salvadoran </LOCATION> government _ backed by the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> _ refuses to compromise in any way. On Monday, they offered loud chants of opposition to <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> policies, yelling: `` No violence, no war, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> out of <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION>,'' and `` Hey hey, ho ho, the Pentagon has got to go.''
