<HEAD>Seven Jobseekers Killed In Melee</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A crowd of people seeking jobs trampled seven people to death today in the East Java capital of <LOCATION> Surabaya </LOCATION>, police said. A Surabaya police officer said hundreds of young men and women suddenly started pushing and shoving after lining up since early in the morning to present their applications for jobs offered by the governor's office. `` Apparently some of them became impatient. Two men and five women were killed in the melee,'' said an officer, who spoke on condition of anonymity. He said a number of other people were injured but gave no figure. No arrests were made and police were investigating the causes of the incident, he said. No further details were immediately available.
