<HEAD>Israeli-American Lobbying Group's Hard Line Comes Under Challenge</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BARRY SCHWEID</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Diplomatic Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Three prominent American Jewish groups are charging that hard-line lobbying for <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> is out of step with `` the consensus of the organized Jewish community.'' The attack on the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Israel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Affairs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, an influential <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> lobbying group, surfaced in a letter published Tuesday by <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> and verified as accurate. A senior official of the committee told <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> `` this whole episode is bound to confuse members of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>.'' The committee is the principal pro-Israel lobbying group in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> and concentrates its efforts on <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. The attack came from leaders of the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jewish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jewish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and the Anti-Defamation League of B'nai B'rith. They disagreed in the letter with <ORGANIZATION> AIPAC </ORGANIZATION>'s opposition to a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> missile sale to <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION>, an oil-rich Arab country; the lobbying group's attempt to force the closing of the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>'s mission to the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION>; and the committee's campaign to deny a visa to <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Yasser </PER