ION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Law </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION>, was at the library Tuesday researching women's unions in the 1940s for a legal history class. `` This is the only library where I could find this material,'' she said. Museum staffer <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Falk </PERSON> said that for years women studying at colleges in the area were unaware of the library's existence. `` All of sudden, though, women are a legitimate field of study,'' she said. The renovation of the existing 1908 building was financed by more than 3,500 gifts and grants.
