10th graf pvs, Macmillan agreed ...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 British publisher <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON> said today he will appeal a <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> judge's refusal to overturn a key element in <ORGANIZATION> Macmillan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s buyout agreement with a rival suitor. <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON> said he also planned to seek an order barring the consummation of the rival group's tender offer for the publishing and information services giant. <PERSON> Macmillan </PERSON> has agreed to a $ 2.5 billion buyout by the investment firm <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kravis </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Roberts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Macmillan </ORGANIZATION> senior management. <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON> has offered $ 2.51 billion for <ORGANIZATION> Macmillan </ORGANIZATION> under certain conditions, and both sides have tender offers out that are scheduled to expire at 12:01 a.m. EDT Wednesday. On Monday, <PERSON> Jack </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Jacobs </PERSON>, a judge in <ORGANIZATION> Delaware </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chancery </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Wilmington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Del. </LOCATION>, denied <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON>'s request for an injunction against a `` lockup provision'' that <PERSON> Macmillan </PERSON> granted <LOCATION> Kohlberg </LOCATION> in case its buyout offer failed. The provision gives the <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> group the right to buy four of <ORGANIZATION> Macmillan </ORGANIZATION>'s businesses for $ 865 million should the merger fail to materialize. <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON>, who is making his bid through his <ORGANIZATION> Maxwell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communication </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, had argued that the provision was unfair and said he would be willing to pay $ 900 million for the same units, which include the Berlitz language centers, the directory division, the direct marketing division and a division that publishes state legal codes. But <PERSON> Macmillan </PERSON> argued that the provision was needed to persuade the <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> group to raise its bid for the company. In today's statement, <ORGANIZATION> Maxwell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communication </ORGANIZATION> said it `` intends to appeal the court's decision and will move today in the appropriate courts for an injunction barring the consummation of <ORGANIZATION> KKR </ORGANIZATION>'s tender offer and barring <PERSON> Macmillan </PERSON> from entering into any transactions out of the ordinary course of business pending that appeal.'' When the company concluded an auction for itself late last month, <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON> offered $ 89 a share in cash for its 27.8 million shares, while <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> offered $ 90.05 a share in cash and securities. <PERSON> Macmillan </PERSON> agreed to the <LOCATION> Kohlberg </LOCATION> offer, but <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON> subsequently raised his offer to $ 90.25 a share in cash. <PERSON> Jacobs </PERSON> said in his ruling that while `` the auction procedures were deficient in several respects ... the evidence is not sufficient to persuade the court that those infirmities were responsible in a legal sense for <PERSON> Macmillan </PERSON> not receiving -LRB- <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON>'s -RRB- highest bid before the auction gavel fell.'' The judge did grant <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON>'s request for an injunction against <ORGANIZATION> Macmillan </ORGANIZATION>'s poison-pill defense, which could have been used to dilute his stake in the company if he were to begin to accumulate <PERSON> Macmillan </PERSON> stock. The judge said he granted the request on condition that <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON> proceed with his offer. Among <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON>'s options are to appeal the decision to a higher court. He had conditioned his tender offer on, among other things, the elimination of both the poison pill provision and the lockup option. He had argued that if <PERSON> Kohlberg </PERSON> were allowed to buy the four units, <PERSON> Macmillan </PERSON> would be left with a $ 250 million tax liability on the sale.
