<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> MCI </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday its earnings rose nearly six-fold in the third quarter on a 40.8 percent rise in revenue. <ORGANIZATION> MCI </ORGANIZATION>, the nation's second-largest long-distance company, said its net income rose to a record $ 99 million, or 38 cents per share, in the three months ended Sept. 30 compared with $ 17 million, or 6 cents per share, in 1987. Third-quarter revenue rose to a record $ 1.4 billion for the quarter, compared with $ 994 million for the same period last year. The company said earnings were driven by strong revenue growth from sales of 800-line and international services and gains in commercial accounts as well as improved operating margins. `` Our success in increasing both volume and market share while controlling costs has allowed us to take full advantage of the high operating leverage that is fundamental to this industry,'' said <PERSON> Bert </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Roberts </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> MCI </ORGANIZATION> president and chief operating officer. <ORGANIZATION> MCI </ORGANIZATION> said the third quarter results included a pre-tax gain of $ 11 million from previously negotiated antitrust settlements and a pre-tax charge of $ 8 million associated with a contract settlement. Results for the third quarter of 1987 included a pre-tax gain of $ 2 million from antitrust settlements. The results for this year's quarter also reflected a 7.35 percent dividend on $ 400 million of preferred stock that was issued to <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> in August. <ORGANIZATION> MCI </ORGANIZATION> also completed the repurchase of about 47 million shares of common stock from <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION>. For the nine months ended Sept. 30, <ORGANIZATION> MCI </ORGANIZATION> earnings rose more than fivefold to $ 219 million, or 78 cents per share, from $ 41 million, or 14 cents per share, a year earlier. Nine-month revenue rose 27.6 percent to $ 3.7 billion from $ 2.9 billion a year earlier.
