<HEAD>PPG Posts 24 Percent Profit Gain in 3rd Qtr</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> PPG </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday its third-quarter profit climbed 24 percent from a year ago as its glass, chemicals and coating and resins businesses each showed improvement. The company reported earnings of $ 112.9 million, or $ 1.03 per share, in the three months ended Sept. 30 compared with $ 91.3 million, or 76 cents a share, a year earlier. Third-quarter revenue rose 8 percent to $ 1.36 billion from $ 1.26 billion a year earlier. For the first nine months, the company earned $ 365.3 million, or $ 3.32 per share, up 30 percent from $ 280.6 million, or $ 2.34 per share, a year earlier. Nine-month revenue rose 9 percent to $ 4.19 billion from $ 3.86 billion a year earlier. `` All of <ORGANIZATION> PPG </ORGANIZATION>'s major business segments _ glass, coatings and resins, and chemicals _ registered sales and operating earnings growth for both the quarter and nine-month period,'' said Chairman <PERSON> Vincent </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sarni </PERSON>. He said the company expects to achieve record sales, earnings and return on equity for the year.
