<HEAD>Illinois First State to Sign International Securities Agreement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An agreement between <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION> and a British agency to share securities information is the first of its kind between a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> state and a foreign regulatory body, a state association said Tuesday. `` Illinois' agreement with the British underscores the vital role that the states can play in policing our increasingly interconnected securities markets,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Baldwin </PERSON>, president of the <ORGANIZATION> North </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administrators </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ' </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> `` Much of the securities enforcement in the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> is carried out at the state level,'' he said. `` So it makes good sense that state securities agencies should play a crucial role in the oversight of global securities markets.'' The accord was signed Oct. 12 by <ORGANIZATION> Illinois </ORGANIZATION> Secretary of State <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Edgar </PERSON> and <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Wilkinson </PERSON>, director of enforcement for <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Great </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>, the largest stock market self-regulatory organization operating under the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kingdom </LOCATION>'s Financial Services Act However, the pact was not announced until the national organization representing 50 state securities agencies `` received a firm indication that <ORGANIZATION> TSA </ORGANIZATION>'s board would approve it at their next meeting Nov. 7,'' said <PERSON> Scott </PERSON> <PERSON> Staff </PERSON>, a spokesman for the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> group. It is similar to an agreement between <ORGANIZATION> TSA </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> and to ones reached recently between the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> and Canadian provinces and territories, the <ORGANIZATION> NASAA </ORGANIZATION> said. Under the accord, the <ORGANIZATION> Illinois </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> association </ORGANIZATION> will exchange information on securities transactions from their respective files for enforcement and regulatory purposes. `` This agreement further establishes <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION> as a world financial leader,'' said <PERSON> Edgar </PERSON>, who oversees the activities of the state's securities department. `` The securities market today is global in character, so regulation and enforcement should be global as well.''
