<HEAD>Third-Quarter Profits Up for Health Care Companies</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Strong gains in third-quarter earnings were reported Tuesday by four leading pharmaceutical and health care companies, <ORGANIZATION> Merck </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Pfizer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Eli </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lilly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Products </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, a leading producer of consumer and health care products, also reported a rise in after-tax profit, and <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cyanamid </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, a pharmaceutical and chemicals concern, said its operating profit rose strongly <ORGANIZATION> Merck </ORGANIZATION> said its net profit rose 31 percent, <ORGANIZATION> Pfizer </ORGANIZATION> had a 17 percent gain, <ORGANIZATION> Lilly </ORGANIZATION> a 14 percent rise and <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> a 16 percent increase. <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Products </ORGANIZATION> reported an 11 percent gain and <ORGANIZATION> Cyanamid </ORGANIZATION> a 17 percent rise. <PERSON> Merck </PERSON>, based in <LOCATION> Rahway </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>, said net income for the quarter totaled $ 311.8 million, or 79 cents a share, on sales of $ 1.47 billion. That compared to a profit of $ 237.6 million, or 58 cents a share, on sales of $ 1.31 billion a year ago. For the nine months, <ORGANIZATION> Merck </ORGA