e, up 50 percent from $ 98.3 million, $ 1.24 a share, a year ago. Revenue rose 9 percent to $ 1.7 billion from $ 1.6 billion. <PERSON> McClatchy </PERSON> said its third-quarter profit fell 3.6 percent to $ 7.2 million, or 25 cents a share, from $ 7.5 million, or 29 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenues rose 6 percent to $ 88.3 million from $ 83.3 million. The company, a <LOCATION> Sacramento </LOCATION>, Calif.-based publisher of daily and community newspapers, cited softness in advertising and increased newsprint costs for the decline. Profit for the first nine months rose 10.3 percent to $ 19.2 million, or 68 cents a share, from $ 17.4 million, or 66 cents a share, in 1987. Revenues rose 7.4 percent to $ 261.3 million from $ 243.4 million. Media General, based in <LOCATION> Richmond </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, said it earned $ 10.8 million, or 38 cents a share, in the latest three months, the same as a year earlier. Third-quarter revenue rose 2 percent to $ 181.8 million from $ 177.5 million. The company's newspaper division had decreased earnings, while results from its newsprint division rose. It said operating profit for the northern <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> cable system are above forecasts. The company said that nine-month earnings totaled $ 38.4 million, or $ 1.34 per share, up 22 percent from $ 31.5 million, or $ 1.10 a share, a year earlier. Nine-month revenue rose 6 percent to $ 564.4 million from $ 531.5 million a year ago.
